talking about something else,

00:47:00.160 --> 00:47:01.870
because somebody --
you said, you know,

00:47:01.870 --> 00:47:03.540
how much you appreciate
this candidate.

00:47:03.540 --> 00:47:04.840
And, somebody said that
makes you an idiot.

00:47:04.840 --> 00:47:07.070
And, then you're talking about gun
control, and then you're talking

00:47:07.070 --> 00:47:11.380
about the economy, and then
you're talking about whatever.

00:47:11.380 --> 00:47:15.840
And -- and that's how the
Talmud organizes information.

00:47:15.840 --> 00:47:18.680
And, Maimonides organizes
information systematically.

00:47:18.680 --> 00:47:22.190
Point one, point two, point
three, definition of terms,

00:47:22.190 --> 00:47:24.430
implications of those
definitions of terms.

00:47:24.430 --> 00:47:27.480
And, Maimonides was
trying to undercut.

00:47:27.480 --> 00:47:29.400
And, who wins in these editions?

00:47:29.400 --> 00:47:30.870
In these editions that
we're looking at,

00:47:30.870 --> 00:47:34.070
these 16th century
edition, the Talmud wins.

00:47:34.070 --> 00:47:35.480
I mean, Maimonides wins also,

00:47:35.480 --> 00:47:37.140
because he becomes
part of the canon.

00:47:37.140 --> 00:47:41.430
But, his core conception of how
information is to be transmitted

00:47:41.430 --> 00:47:45.130
and discussed and organizes
loses in the face of the Talmud.

00:47:45.130 --> 00:47:47.990
The Talmud emerges victorious.

00:47:47.990 --> 00:47:49.550
It's not organized.

00:47:49.550 --> 00:47:51.750
